Author: Renlywinsthethrone
Text: I've been struggling with disordered eating for over 11 years and this always fluctuates for me. Some years weight loss feels effortless. Some years all I can do is maintain. Some years I just gain and gain and gain. Cycle repeats. The only thing that's constant is that I feel just as bad about myself at my low weights as a do at my high ones, and even when everyone around me notices and compliments my weight loss I can't stop feeling like nothing changed.
